$ %SystemRoot%\System32\drivers

Most files in `%SystemRoot%\System32\drivers` have the suffix `.sys` and correspond to a → Windows/services[service].
-
The files are referenced by the value of → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Services/_driver_name_#reg-services-imagePath[`ImagePath`]
under the driver's corresponding → Windows/registry[registry] key
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Services/_driver_name_[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\driverName`].

The directory contains the *core driver files* for Direct X, Volume Manager, → development/web/TCP-IP[TCP/IP] and → hardware/ACPI[ACPI].

sa:
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Services[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services`]

  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/driverquery_exe[`driverquery.exe`]
